President Obama spoke with President Joseph Kabila of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) and emphasized the importance of timely and peaceful elections that respect the DRC's constitution and protect the rights of all citizens. President Obama also assured President Kabila that the United States would remain engaged in the DRC throughout the electoral process, including through the appointment of a new U.S. Special Envoy. The two leaders reaffirmed their commitment to ending the threat of armed groups, particularly the FDLR. President Obama also discussed the pending adoptions in the DRC by American families and urged a timely resolution.